PBS

```json
{
  "software": [
    "R",
    "Stan",
    "anaconda3",
    "PBS"
  ],
  "resources": {
    "walltime": "08:00:00",
    "cpus": 4,
    "memory": "50gb",
    "storage": [
      "/rds/general/user/sd121/home/bayes-rate-consistency",
      "/rds/general/user/sd121/home/bayes-rate-consistency-output"
    ]
  }
}
```

This script is designed to be run using the PBS (Portable Batch System) workload manager. It uses R, Stan, and Anaconda to simulate datasets, run Stan models, and perform post-processing. The script requires 4 CPU cores, 50GB of RAM, and 8 hours of walltime. It also utilizes two storage locations: `/rds/general/user/sd121/home/bayes-rate-consistency` and `/rds/general/user/sd121/home/bayes-rate-consistency-output`.
